      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CONNECTOR (8) was quickly into stride on debut to score by 1.5 lengths (17.45) at this track over 300m. Boxed wide but has the pace to be prominent. Can make it back to back wins. Can continue winning ways. MISS PIPER (1) had a tricky draw last time and although midfield in fifth wasn't far away finishing 3.5 lengths from the winner (17.75). Yet to win here but has run some good races. Can figure in the finish. LEFEVRE RICO (4) was responsible for a modest effort most recently when sixth at Mt Gambier over 305m behind Pressure Point (18.51) in a TG1-4W. Placed at his previous run. The form from his last run stacks up well. Shapes as one to consider. CRITICAL MASS (7) was out of the money here last time out but can bounce back.",
